{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\nouicompat{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Segoe UI;}{\f1\fswiss\fcharset0 Segoe UI;}{\f2\fswiss Segoe UI;}{\f3\fnil\fcharset1 Cambria Math;}{\f4\fnil Segoe UI;}{\f5\fnil\fcharset0 Cambria Math;}} {\colortbl ;\red0\green102\blue204;\red51\green153\blue102;} {\*\generator Riched20 10.0.26100}{\*\mmathPr\mmathFont3\mwrapIndent1440 }\viewkind4\uc1 \pard\cf1\b\f0\fs28\lang9 SkyeClip Help\par \par \cf2\f1\fs24 Overview\par \cf0\b0\par SkyeClip is a lightweight clipboard manager that stores your recent clips, lets you mark favorites, and provides quick access through the tray menu and hotkeys.\par \cf2\b\par Tray Menu\par \cf0\b0 To make it easier to identify the type of content stored in each clip, SkyeClip adds small format indicators to the end of the preview text. Clips that contain Rich Text Format data will include the suffix <RTF>. Clips that contain HTML data will include the suffix <HTML>. These indicators appear only in the preview list to help you quickly understand what formats are available for each clip. The full Clip Viewer still shows the complete content using the appropriate viewer (plain text, rich text, HTML, image, or file list)\par \cf2\b\par Tray Menu HotKeys (Customizable)\par \cf0\par \b0\i <F>\par Toggle Favorite\par \i0 Marks or unmarks the selected clip as a Favorite. Favorited clips appear in the Favorites menu for quick access.\par \b\par \b0\i <V>\par Show Clip Viewer\par \i0 Opens the Clip Viewer,\f2 a compact companion window that displays the full contents of the selected clip.\par \par \i\f1\lang1033 <S>\i0\par Show Scratch Pad\par Opens the Scratch Pad with the selected clip appended to the current text, if any.\f2\lang9\par \par \cf2\b\f1 Favorites\par \par \cf0\b0 Favorites let you keep important clips accessible at all times.\par \i How to use:\i0\par - Press Spacebar on a clip\par - Or right\f2\_click \f3\u8594?\f1 Toggle Favorite\par - Favorites appear in their own menu for quick access\par \cf2\b\lang9\par Clip Viewer\par \cf0\b0\par The Clip Viewer displays the full text of the selected clip.\par Useful for reading long clips without having to paste somewhere.\par \i Features:\i0\par - View full clip contents\par - Keyboard shortcut <Ctrl+C> to copy to clipboard\par \par \cf2\b Scratch Pad\cf0\b0\f2\par \par Scratch Pad is a lightweight, always\_available editor built into SkyeClip. It\rquote s designed for quick notes, temporary text, code snippets, and anything you want to keep handy while working. Scratch Pad supports both Rich Text (RTF) and Plain Text, and you can import or export content at any time.\par \par \i Keyboard Shortcuts\par Standard Editing\par \i0 Ctrl+Z\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Undo\par Ctrl+X\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Cut \f1\lang1033 S\f2\lang9 elected \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par Ctrl+C\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Copy \f1\lang1033 S\f2\lang9 elected \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par Ctrl+V\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Paste \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par \f1\lang1033 Ctrl+D = Delete Text\f2\lang9\par Ctrl+A\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Select \f1\lang1033 A\f2\lang9 ll \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par \i Shift\_Modified Variants\f1\lang1033 (\f2\lang9 Some shortcuts behave differently when Shift is held\f1\lang1033 )\f2\lang9\par \i0\f1\lang1033 Shift+Ctrl+C = Redo\par Shift+Ctrl+X = Cut as Plain T\f2\lang9 ext (\f1\lang1033 S\f2\lang9 trips \f1\lang1033 F\f2\lang9 ormatting\f1\lang1033 )\f2\lang9\par Shift+Ctrl+C\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Copy \f1\lang1033 a\f2\lang9 s \f1\lang1033 Pl\f2\lang9 ain \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext (\f1\lang1033 S\f2\lang9 trips \f1\lang1033 F\f2\lang9 ormatting)\par Shift+Ctrl+V\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Paste \f1\lang1033 a\f2\lang9 s \f1\lang1033 P\f2\lang9 lain \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par \par \i\f1\lang1033 C\f2\lang9 ontext Menu\par \i0\f1\lang1033 Undo/Redo = Undo (If available)\par Shift+Undo/Redo = Redo (If available)\par Cut = Cut Selected Text\par Shift+Cut = Cut As Plain Text\par \f2\lang9 Copy\f1\lang1033 = \f2\lang9 Copies \f1\lang1033 S\f2\lang9 elected \f1\lang1033 T\f2\lang9 ext\par \f1\lang1033 Shift+Copy = Copies as Plain Text\f2\lang9\par \f1\lang1033 Paste = Paste Text\par Shift+Paste = Paste as Plain Text\par Delete = Delete Text\par Select All = Select All Text\f2\lang9\par \par \i Keep Text Between Sessions\i0\par Scratch Pad includes a Keep Text toggle. When enabled\f1\lang1033 , y\f2\lang9 our text is automatically saved when you close \f1\lang1033 the Scratch Pad. \f2\lang9 It is restored exactly as you left it\f1\lang1033 . \f2\lang9 When disabled, Scratch Pad starts empty each time \f1\lang1033 you open it\f2\lang9 .\par \par \i Exporting Content\i0\par You can export your Scratch Pad content at any time. Scratch Pad supports\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 Rich Text (.rtf)\f1\lang1033 and \f2\lang9 preserves formatting\f1\lang1033 , as well as \f2\lang9 Plain Text (.txt)\f1\lang1033 that\f2\lang9 saves clean Unicode text\f1\lang1033 . \f2\lang9 Scratch Pad automatically chooses the correct format based on the file extension you select.\par \par \i Importing Content\f1\lang1033\par \i0\f2\lang9 You can import\f1\lang1033 Rich Text (\f2\lang9 .rtf\f1\lang1033 )\f2\lang9 files\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 with formatting\f1\lang1033 , as well as Plain Text (\f2\lang9 .txt\f1\lang1033 )\f2\lang9 files\f1\lang1033 . \f2\lang9 Imported content replaces whatever is currently in Scratch Pad.\par \f1\par \cf2\b Save Clip To File\par \cf0\b0\par SkyeClip lets you save any stored clip as a standalone file on your computer. This is useful when you want to keep a copy outside the clipboard history, share a clip with someone else, or archive important content.\par \par \i What You Can Save\i0\par SkyeClip supports saving every major clipboard format:\par - Text clips saved as .txt (Unicode Text), .rtf (Rich Text), or .html (HTML Fragment).\par - Image clips saved as .png, .jpg, or .bmp.\par - File drops (files copied in Explorer) saved as .zip archive containing all copied files and folders.\par - Binary / unknown formats saved as .bin (raw clipboard data).\par \par SkyeClip automatically detects the clip\rquote s format and offers the appropriate export options.\par \par \i How To Save A Clip\i0\par You can save a clip from the main Tray context menu, the Clip Explorer context menu, or from the floating button in Clip Viewer.\f2\par \f1\par \cf2\b Clip Explorer\par \cf0\b0\par Clip Explorer provides a fast, organized view of your clipboard history. It\rquote s designed as a simple browser for past clips, letting you quickly find, preview, and reuse anything you\rquote ve copied.\par \i\par What Clip Explorer Shows\i0\par A list of your recent clips\par A preview of the text for each item\par Helpful details like when the clip was created and whether it\rquote s a favorite\par \par \i What You Can Do\i0\par Browse your clipboard history in a clean, scrollable list\par Preview clips without opening the viewer\par Use Clip to restore an item back to the clipboard\par Open in Viewer for a detailed look\par Favorite important clips for quick access\par Filter by favorites, age, or text type\par \par \i When to Use Clip Explorer\i0\par Use Clip Explorer when you want a quick overview of your clipboard history without digging through menus. It\rquote s ideal for finding something you copied earlier today, comparing similar clips, or jumping back to a favorite you saved some time earlier.\par \par \cf2\b Profiles\par \cf0\b0\f0 SkyeClip includes an optional Profile System that allows you to maintain completely separate clipboard environments within the same application. Profiles are ideal for users who switch between different workflows\f4\emdash\f0 such as personal use, development, work, or creative projects\f4\emdash\f0 and want each environment to feel clean, organized, and independent. Profiles affect how SkyeClip stores, displays, and manages your clipboard history, favorites, and certain settings.\par \par \i What Profiles Do\i0\par When Profiles are enabled:\par - Each profile has its own clipboard history\par - Each profile has its own Favorites\par - Each profile has its own settings, including:\par
\pard\li720 - Theme / Theme Auto\par - Max Clips\par - Max Clip Preview Length\par - Blink on New Clip\par - Notify on New Clip\par - Play Sound with Notification\par
\pard - The Scratch Pad saves its content separately per profile (if Scratch Pad Keep Text is enabled)\par - Switching profiles instantly changes the active environment\par This allows you to keep your personal and work/development clipboards completely separate.\par \par \i Enabling Profiles\i0\par Profiles can be enabled in Settings \f3\u8594?\f0 Profiles.\par Once enabled, SkyeClip will:\par - Allow switching between profiles from the Profile Tray Menu\par - Save and load profile\f4\_\f0 specific settings automatically\par \par \i Switching Profiles\i0\par You can switch profiles at any time using the Profile Tray Menu\par When switching profiles:\par - Your current clipboard list is saved\par - The new profile\f4\rquote\f0 s clipboard list is loaded\par - The theme and other per\f4\_\f0 profile settings update immediately\par - Scratch Pad content is saved per profile (if enabled)\par SkyeClip ensures switching is safe and does not lose data.\par \par \i Profile Settings\i0\par Some settings apply per profile. Each profile stores its own values for:\par - Theme\f5 / \f0 Theme\f5 \f0 Auto\f5 : \f0 Controls\f5 \f0 the\f5 \f0 visual\f5 \f0 appearance\f5 \f0 for\f5 \f0 this\f5 \f0 profile\par - Max\f5 \f0 Clips\f5 : \f0 Maximum\f5 \f0 number\f5 \f0 of\f5 \f0 clipboard\f5 \f0 entries\f5 \f0 shown\f5 \f0 for\f5 \f0 this\f5 \f0 profile\par - Max\f5 \f0 Clip\f5 \f0 Preview\f5 \f0 Length\f5 : \f0 Amount\f5 \f0 of\f5 \f0 text\f5 \f0 shown\f5 \f0 in\f5 \f0 each\f5 \f0 clip\f5 \f0 preview\par - Blink\f5 \f0 on\f5 \f0 New\f5 \f0 Clip\f5 : \f0 Whether\f5 \f0 the\f5 \f0 tray\f5 \f0 icon\f5 \f0 blinks\f5 \f0 when\f5 \f0 a\f5 \f0 new\f5 \f0 clip\f5 \f0 is\f5 \f0 captured\par - Notify\f5 \f0 on\f5 \f0 New\f5 \f0 Clip: Shows\f5 \f0 a\f5 \f0 notification\f5 \f0 when\f5 \f0 a\f5 \f0 new\f5 \f0 clip\f5 \f0 is\f5 \f0 captured\par - Play\f5 \f0 Sound\f5 \f0 with\f5 \f0 Notification: Plays\f5 \f0 a\f5 \f0 sound\f5 \f0 when\f5 \f0 a\f5 \f0 new\f5 \f0 clip\f5 \f0 arrives\par These settings override the global defaults whenever Profiles are enabled. Setting controls that are per-profile are marked with a small profile icon badge to indicate that changing them affects only the currently selected profile. A banner at the top of the Settings page shows which profile is being edited.\par \par \i Managing Profiles\i0\par You can:\par - Create new profiles\par - Rename profiles\par - Reorder profiles (drag to reorder)\par - Delete profiles\par SkyeClip automatically saves profile order, settings, and clipboard data.\par \par \i Clip Explorer and Profiles\i0\par Clip Explorer fully supports profiles:\par - You can view clips from the current profile\par - Or toggle to show all profiles\par - You can move clips between profiles (Favorites or regular clips)\par - Profile names appear in the Profile column when enabled\par This makes it easy to reorganize or migrate clips between environments.\par \par \i When Profiles Are Disabled\i0\par If Profiles are turned off:\par - SkyeClip uses the global settings\par - All clipboard data is stored in a single shared list\par - Scratch Pad uses a single shared text buffer\par - Profile\f4\_\f0 specific settings are ignored until Profiles are re\f4\_\f0 enabled\par Your profile data is preserved and will be restored when Profiles are turned back on\lang1033 .\cf2\b\lang9\par \f1\par Rules Overview\cf0\b0\par Rules let SkyeClip react automatically to your current context. Each rule watches for a specific condition\f2\emdash such as the app you\rquote re using, the network you\rquote re connected to, the time of day, or the content of the clipboard\emdash and performs an action when that condition becomes true. Rules help SkyeClip stay out of your way, protect your privacy, and switch profiles automatically when needed.\par SkyeClip supports \f1\lang1033 six\f2\lang9 types of rules: App Rules, Location Rules, Time Rules,\f1\lang1033 Source\f2\lang9 Rules\f1\lang1033 , Keyword Rules, and Format Rules\f2\lang9 . Each rule type has its own condition and can trigger actions such as switching profiles or blocking clipboard capture.\par \par \i App Rules\i0\par App Rules trigger when a specific application becomes active.\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 These are useful when different apps require different clipboard behavior.\par Examples:\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Work\rdblquote profile when Outlook or Teams is active.\par - Block clipboard capture when using a password manager.\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Creative\rdblquote profile when Photoshop is active.\par App Rules activate as soon as the chosen app \f1\lang1033 is started or stopped, or \f2\lang9 becomes the foreground window.\par \par \i Location Rules\i0\par Location Rules trigger based on the network you\rquote re currently connected to.\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 SkyeClip detects your Wi\_Fi SSID or network name and applies the rule when it matches.\par Examples:\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Home\rdblquote profile when connected to your home Wi\_Fi.\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Work\rdblquote profile when connected to your office network.\par - Block clipboard capture automatically on public Wi\_Fi.\par Location Rules update whenever your network connection changes.\par \par \i Time Rules\i0\par Time Rules trigger based on the current time of day\f1\lang1033 . \f2\lang9 They\rquote re useful for predictable routines or scheduled behavior changes.\par Examples:\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Work\rdblquote profile during work hours.\par - Switch to a \ldblquote Personal\rdblquote profile in the evening.\par - Block clipboard capture overnight.\par Time Rules activate when the system clock enters the defined time range.\par \par \i Content Rules\i0\par Content Rules\f1\lang1033 based on Source, Keyword, or Format\f2\lang9 trigger based on what\rquote s currently in the clipboard.\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 They can match \f1\lang1033 the sending app, \f2\lang9 keywords, detect formats, or react to specific types of content.\par Examples:\par - Auto\_favorite clips containing certain keywords.\par - Block clipboard capture when sensitive content is detected.\par - \f1\lang1033 Auto-ignore \f2\lang9 when copying specific types of data.\par Content Rules activate whenever the clipboard changes and the content matches the rule.\par \par \i Actions\i0\par Each rule can perform one or more actions when its condition becomes true:\par - Switch Profile\f1\lang1033 , \f2\lang9 chang\f1\lang1033 ing\f2\lang9 SkyeClip\rquote s active profile automatically.\par - Block Clipboard Capture\f1\lang1033 , \f2\lang9 prevent\f1\lang1033 ing\f2\lang9 SkyeClip from saving clipboard history while still showing the live clipboard preview.\par - Auto\_Favorite\f1\lang1033 , \f2\lang9 mark\f1\lang1033 ing\f2\lang9 matching clips as favorites for quick access.\par \f1\lang1033 - Auto-Ignore, preventing capture based on the content of the clip.\f2\lang9\par Actions remain in effect until the rule\rquote s condition is no longer true.\par \par \i How Rules Work Together\par \i0 Multiple rules can be active at the same time.\par If more than one rule applies, SkyeClip uses the most recent rule that became active. When a rule stops matching, SkyeClip returns to the previous state or profile.\f1\lang1033 \f2\lang9 Rules are evaluated continuously as your context changes\emdash apps, networks, time, and clipboard content.\par \par Tips for Using Rules\par - Keep rules simple and focused on one behavior.\par - Use profiles to group settings and let rules switch between them.\par - Use Location Rules for privacy and safety on public networks.\par - Use App Rules to tailor SkyeClip to your workflow.\par - Use Content Rules to automate repetitive tasks or protect sensitive data.\par \cf2\b\f1\par App View\cf0\b0\par \par The App View is a compact control panel that provides quick access to SkyeClip\rquote s core features. It appears as a small window with buttons for common tasks, making it easy to navigate without opening a full application.\par \i Included functions:\i0\par - Settings \f2\emdash Configure hotkeys, limits, and behavior\par - Log Viewer \emdash View SkyeClip\rquote s internal activity log\par - Help \emdash Open this help guide\par - About \emdash View version information and credits\par \f1\lang1033 - Exit App\lang9\par \par \cf2\b Settings\par \cf0\b0\par SkyeClip allows customization of:\par - Hotkeys\par - Maximum viewed clips\par - Whether or not to notify the user of new clips on the clipboard\par - Purge Functions\par - and more\par \par \cf2\b Automatic Backups\par \cf0\b0\par SkyeClip can create periodic backups of your clipboard database according to your selected schedule.\par \par \i Backup Frequency Options\i0\par - Never\par - Every Day\par - Every Other Day\par - Every Three Days\par - Every Week\par - Every Other Week\par - Every Month\par Backups are stored in your SkyeClip data folder using a timestamped filename.\par If enabled, SkyeClip can also automatically purge older backup files to conserve space.\par \par \i Backup Behavior\par \i0 - Runs silently in the background\par - Uses the same safe backup routine as manual backups\par - Logs all backup activity\par \par \i Manual Control\i0\par You can still perform manual backups at any time.\par Automatic maintenance never interferes with manual actions.\par \par \par }
